<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-576-882  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 576 882.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 22 1989 v3 n31 p5(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Claris eases CAD file exchange. (Claris Graphics Translator)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Garner, Rochelle.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Claris Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Claris Graphics Translator (Utility program) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionUtility ProgramsComputer-Aided DesignFile Transfer.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Claris eases CAD file exchangeandM;Santa Clara, Calif.andP;  -- Claris Corp. this month delivered its Claris GraphicsTRanslator, a $299 program that lets users exchange files between Claris CADand other CAD programs via standard graphic formats.andM;The translator supports IGES (initial graphic exchange specification) 3 and4, DXF (Drawing Interchange Format) 9 and 10, and MacDraw II and PICTformats.andM;While Claris Graphics TRanslator will not translate Claris CAD's underlyingdatabase, it will transfer all the geometry, layering and line stylescontained in a CAD documents.andP;  Users can also select portions of the geometryfor translation, employ the Preview mode to make sure the translation will beaccurate, and set up a queue of tasks for later execution.andM;The software was originally due in March.andP;  &quot;We've been working with more than30 customers with industrial-strength drawings to make sure we have solidtranslations,&quot; said Mel Badgett, Claris CAD product manager.andM;The program runs on SEs and IIs.andP;  It needs at least 2 Mbytes of memory foruse with large monitors, 256 colors of MultiFinder.andM;Claris Corp, is located at 5201 Patric Henry Drive, Box 58168, Santa Clara,Calif.andP;  95052-8168; (408) 987-7000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>